Colombia’s EPM Telecom Sells 300 Billion Pesos of Securities

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-10-20T19:49:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/colombia-s-epm-telecom-sells-300-billion-pesos-of-securities.html
Empresas Publicas de Medellin SA’s
telecommunications unit sold 300 billion pesos ($157.2 million)
worth of inflation-linked bonds in the local market.  UNE EPM Telecomunicaciones SA, or UNE, as the company is
known, sold five- and 12-year securities to yield 3.67 and 4.76
percentage points above inflation, respectively, the stock
exchange said in a statement. Demand for the bonds totaled 417.6
billion pesos, according to the statement.  Correval SA brokerage managed the sale. Empresas Publicas
de Medellin, or EPM, is a Medellin-based regional utility
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
